# Code owners for smart-router-dashboard.
#
# GitHub auto-requests a review from the matching owner on every PR that
# touches a path below, and (when "Require review from Code Owners" is on
# in branch protection) that review is required to merge.
#
# Order matters: the LAST matching pattern wins. The catch-all comes first
# so more specific rules below can override it.

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
*                       @Magma-Devs/r-d

# Release & supply-chain surface — changes here build and publish the
# GHCR images, so they're pinned out explicitly to make the blast radius
# obvious in review.
/.github/workflows/     @Magma-Devs/r-d
/v2/apps/api/Dockerfile @Magma-Devs/r-d
/v2/apps/web/Dockerfile @Magma-Devs/r-d

# Licensing & legal text — keep dual-license wording under review so a
# stray edit can't quietly change the commercial terms.
/LICENSE.md             @Magma-Devs/r-d
/LICENSING.md           @Magma-Devs/r-d
